-- England Trails Australia by 408 Runs in Third Ashes Cricket Test
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-08-03T12:19:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-03/england-trails-australia-by-408-runs-in-third-ashes-cricket-test.html
England was 119-4 at lunch on day
three of the third Ashes cricket Test and trails Australia by
408 runs.  Kevin Pietersen  is 33 not out at Old Trafford in Manchester
and  Ian Bell  is on four. England captain Alastair Cook scored 62
before being dismissed today by Mitchell Starc, while Ryan
Harris claimed Jonathan Trott for five.  Australia declared its first innings yesterday on 527-7.  England won the first two games of the five-Test series and
would claim the Ashes for the third straight time with a draw or
victory.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  